No, taxes are the perfect analogy: If you leave the country in question, you no longer need to pay tax to that country. If you leave the server, you no longer have to abide by the conventions of it. If you don't abide by the conventions of this server, you are publicly named a big giant fuqtard. This is the community equivilent of prison. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
You referance to rotations is mute as well, since there is no real rotation as recognized by everyone on this mob. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
First of all, the word is &quot;moot&quot;. Mute implies that I was silent. <br>
<br>
Second of all, my referance to rotations is not a moot point simply because *if* you have ever engaged a mob that was on rotation, you have benefitted of the conventions of the server and can no longer try to exclude yourself from those conventions when they don't suit you. The fact that the mob we are currently in a frenzy over is *not* on rotation, is not relevent to the discussion, as the conventions of that camp are well known, and claiming otherwise is bordering on willful blindness and is still inexcusable. <br>
<br>
If you have ever gone to the planes on a reserved date, you cannot then ignore someone else's day because it suits you. You have, by participating in the system and gaining it's benefits, also indirectly consented to the negative side as well (as few as they are).<br>
<br>
The idea is *old*. The Social Contract, old. Rousseau (sp?). <br>
<br>
You know, Hobbes' Leviathan is also present in this community too. <br>
<br>
Funny how microchasms of society are like that.<br>
